		  <td class="forum_boardrow1" style="border-width: 0px 1px 1px 1px;" valign="top"><div id="message31391547">Agh, not the idea channel.<br />
<br />
Anyways, no I don't really think the audience should be considered too much. I'm not one to really enjoy an anime that completely panders to its fans (except when it panders to someone like me, and even then I guess it's shameless that I'd go along with it). I mean pandering to a group more or less kills any creativity and just gives the people what they want. I dunno, I feel like if it's an idea that's been done before, it should really be avoided in a creative process. i.e. Madoka Magica, even though I'm not the biggest fan of it, never pandered in the original series and it felt like it really didn't care too much about its fans. However, In the newest film, Rebellion, there was a good bit of shameless pandering thrown in to seemingly please hardcore fans I'd guess. Kind of just giving them what they'd want and the shock they would expect. This might be appealing to others, but it's not really something I like to see in anime. <br />
<br />
So, I personally think there's something wrong in an anime that aims at appealing a distinct group right out of the gate. This can be said for most anime, but it should be more along the lines of portraying a certain story and letting something like the demographic follow suit. Even if an anime isn't made for a certain person, the themes and messages of a story can relate to the viewer. i.e. picking up the messages from a story and picking out how they apply to you as a viewer, pretty much how it makes you <em>feel</em>. I guess an example of this would be Angel's Egg, an experience I feel that's really melded towards the viewer. I like this because the anime can sort of hold its own experience for the viewer, something nobody else but they experienced while watching it. I dunno, this might be only something viewers like me would delude themselves into thinking, but I really do think that a personal experience towards an anime is important. I feel that this is rather difficult when and anime is boom boom shoot the gun video games and boobz. <br />
<br />
Beep bop a boo bop a wam bam</div><div class="postActions"></div><div class="sig"><strong>получить деньги моего друга</strong></div></td>
