		  <td class="forum_boardrow1" style="border-width: 0px 1px 1px 1px;" valign="top"><div id="message31394243"><!--quote--><div class="quotetext"><strong>lpf said:</strong><!--quotesaid--><br><!--quote--><div class="quotetext"><strong>iSuckAtWriting said:</strong><!--quotesaid--><br>Screenwriters and directors should make that concession to the audience keeping in mind it's entertainment first and foremost.<!--quote--></div>What do you think of the argument that writers shouldn't make something that they don't 'love' and that fewer people will love so that more people 'like' it?<!--quote--></div><br />
