		  <td class="forum_boardrow1" style="border-width: 0px 1px 1px 1px;" valign="top"><div id="message31550909">Certainly, FLCL is a show with a ton of exclusive content, such as other anime/manga and pop culture references.  Many people won't understand all that, and will come to dislike the show.  But what makes this show good is the fast, zany, hyper-kinetic pacing.  They can't really slow down, to provide exposition on all the references and symbolism, or it would really hurt the flow and atmosphere.  Certainly, there's references one might miss after a quick watch-through, and it will probably take 2-3 watches (or pausing/rewinding) to get the most of it, but in this case, I feel that their approach is worthwhile.<br />
<br />
Mind Game and Sayonara Zetsubou are two other shows where the pacing/flow/atmosphere would be affected if the creator tried to spoon-feed the audience, instead of being more abstract in some parts.</div><div class="postActions"></div></td>
